3 Ye who are hardened and far away,
4 Why will you die when there yet is room ?
Come to the cross of Jesus ;
Come to the cross of Jesus;
Hear Him SO tenderly plead to-day,
Why will you perish in sight of home?
Come to the cross of Jesus.
Come to the cross of Jesus.
Though you have slighted His love so long,
What will you do when He comes at last?
Gone with your heart in the ways of wrong,
How can you live till His wrath is past?
Still He will save with His arm SO strong,
Oh, heed His call, it may be the last!
Come to the cross of Jesus.
Come to the cross of Jesus.
